<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: js; gutter: false; theme: Confluence; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Confl=
uence">{
  "creditTransferTransactionInformation": [
    {
      "creditor": {
        "name": "string"
      },
      "creditorAccount": {
        "identification": "string",
        "issuer": "string",
        "name": "string",
        "schemeName": "string",
        "type": "string"
      },
      "creditorAgent": {
        "BICFI": "string"
      },
      "endToEndIdentification": "string",
      "instructedAmount": {
        "amount": "string",
        "currency": "AUD"
      },
      "instructionForDebtorAgent": "string",
      "paymentTypeInformation": { // Object not required from Feb 2026
        "categoryPurpose": "string",
        "instructionPriority": "HIGH",
        "localInstrument": "string",
        "serviceLevel": "string"
      },
      "remittanceInformation": {
        "unstructured": [
          "string"
        ]
      },
      "supplementaryData": {
        "isNewPayee": boolean, // FEB 26 scope
        "aliasId": "string",
        "aliasType": "TELI",
        "beneficiaryId": "string",
        "templateId": "string", // Not required from Feb 2026
        "aliasResolutionTime": "string" // Feb 2026 scope
      }
    }
  ],
  "debtor": {
    "identification": "string",
    "issuer": "string",
    "name": "string"
  },
  "debtorAccount": {
    "identification": "string",
    "issuer": "string",
    "name": "string",
    "schemeName": "string",
    "type": "string"
  },
  "debtorAgent": {
    "BICFI": "string"
  },
  "initiatingParty": {
    "name": "string"
  },
  "instructionForDebtorAgent": "string",
  "paymentInformation": {
    "controlSum": "string", // Not required from Feb 2026
    "numberOfTransactions": "string"
  },
  "paymentMethod": "TRF",
  "paymentTypeInformation": {
    "categoryPurpose": "string",
    "instructionPriority": "HIGH",
    "localInstrument": "string", // Not required from Feb 2026
    "serviceLevel": "string"
  },
  "supplementaryData": {
    "debitDescription": "string",
    "instructionTraceIdentification": "string",
    "divisionId": "string", // Feb 2026 divisions scope
    "matchedCOPStatusCode": "V0C1", // May 2026 CoP scope
    "matchedCOPAccountName": "ABC account" // May 2026 CoP scope
&nbsp; },
  "entitlementData": { // For fund transfer less data is required.
    "supplementaryData": [
      {
        "name": "W1_2FADEVICETYPE",
        "value": "SOFT TOKEN",
        "datatype": "STRING"
      },
      {
        "name": "TENANT",
        "value": "TREASURY",
        "datatype": "STRING"
      },
      {
        "name": "W1C_CURRENCY",
        "value": "to currency e.g. AUD",
        "datatype": "STRING"
      },
      {
        "name": "CROSS_CURRENCY_PAYMENT",
        "value": "true if from and to currency are different",
        "datatype": "STRING"
      },
      {
        "name": "CURRENCY_FROM",
        "value": "from account currency",
        "datatype": "STRING"
      },
      {
        "name": "NEWPAYEE",
        "value": "true if any beneficiary is a first-time payee and false i=
f beneficiary is not first-time payee",
        "datatype": "BOOLEAN"
      },
      {
        "name": "PAYEEDESTINATIONACCOUNT",
        "value": "BSB + account number \u2013  for domestic payments\nSWIFT=
 code + account number/IBAN  \u2013 for international payments \nempty - fo=
r bulk payments (when/if they come in)",
        "datatype": "STRING"
      },
      {
        "name": "PAYEEPAYIDTYPE",
        "value": "MOBILE, EMAIL,LANDLINE, ABN, FREEFORM",
        "datatype": "STRING"
      },
      {
        "name": "PAYEEPAYIDVALUE ",
        "value": "Alias value",
        "datatype": "STRING"
      },
      {
        "name": "PAYEEPAYIDSHORTNAME ",
        "value": "Alias short name",
        "datatype": "STRING"
      },
      {
        "name": "PAYEEPAYIDACCOUNTTYPE",
        "value": "Type of account linked to PayID can be BSB or CC.",
        "datatype": "STRING"
      },
      {
        "name": "PAYIDSHORTNAMECHANGED ",
        "value": "Indicates whether the short name has changed since the al=
ias details were last resolved/recorded (between Create and Auth).",
        "datatype": "STRING"
      }
    ]
  }
}</pre>
</div>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><br></p>
<p>See <a href=3D"/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=3D1812389994">Make a paymen=
t UI - EXP API Mapping [ERM 25E2 - February 2025]</a></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><u><strong>Sept 2025 ERM:</strong></u> As part for maker-checker, <s>a n=
ew object called "entitlements"(as below) will be included in the request b=
ody</s> a new request header called "x-channelRequestId" will be populated =
with the PaymentId. <span style=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Refer to&nbsp;</=
span><a style=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;" href=3D"https://confluence.srv.wes=
tpac.com.au/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=3D1943049094#id-06.SD:MakerandChec=
ker-PaymentsMFEandPaymentsExpAPI-SequenceofchangesrequiredtogeneratePayment=
Idupfront" rel=3D"nofollow">Payments Exp API - Sequence of changes required=
 to generate PaymentId upfront</a><span style=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;">&n=
bsp;for the sequence flow</span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><u><strong>Nov 2025 ERM:</strong></u> As part of Payment Limits, a new r=
equest body attribute/property called "instructionTraceIdentification" will=
 be introduced in the supplementary data object. Refer to the SD here for d=
etails: <a href=3D"/display/ARTC/SD%3A+Payments+Limits+-+Channels#SD:Paymen=
tsLimitsChannels-PaymentsMFEandPaymentsExpAPI-UniqueInstructionTraceId">SD:=
 Payments Limits - Channels#PaymentsMFEandPaymentsExpAPI-UniqueInstructionT=
raceId</a>&nbsp;</p>
<p><br></p>
<p><u><strong>Feb 2026 ERM:</strong></u> As part of beneficiary enhancement=
, a new request body attribute called "<em style=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;"=
>customerCreditTransferInitiation.supplementaryData[0].envelope[0].extensio=
n.</em><span style=3D"color: rgb(205,89,55);"><em>isNewPayee</em></span><sp=
an style=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;">" is introduced to indicate during the =
maker/checker process if the payment is toward an existing beneficiary or a=
 new/unsaved beneficiary.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><span style=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Refer to <a href=3D"https://confl=
uence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/ARTC/Channels+SD+%3A+Payment+Initiation+CA=
P+API+-V1+to+V2+upgrade" rel=3D"nofollow">Channels SD : Payment Initiation =
CAP API -V1 to V2 upgrade - Westpac One Core - Westpac Enterprise Confluenc=
e</a> for the new EXP API mapping.</span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>The field should be passed on to the Payment CAP API accordingly and ret=
rieved from PODS later.</p>
<p>When paying to <span>existing </span>beneficiary, the field is passed wi=
th value false</p>
<p><span style=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;">When paying to new beneficiary, t=
he field is passed with value true</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Refer to SD for detail: <a href=
=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=3D20=
88155282#id-05SD:Beneficiaryenhancements&amp;paymenttemplate-SequenceDiagra=
m" rel=3D"nofollow">05- SD: Beneficiary enhancements &amp; payment template=
 - Westpac One Core - Westpac Enterprise Confluence</a></span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><em>entitlement.supplementaryData </em>has been added for SAFI integrati=
on. ( extra data needs to be passed to SAFI )</p>
<p>for fund transfer, a different payload is required:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>Entitlement payload for fund transfer</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: js; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">   "entit=
lementData": { // For fund transfer less data is required.
    "supplementaryData": [
      {
        "name": "PAYEEDESTINATIONACCOUNT",
        "value": "BSB + account number \u2013  for domestic payments\nSWIFT=
 code + account number/IBAN  \u2013 for international payments \nempty - fo=
r bulk payments (when/if they come in)"
      },
      {
        "name": "PAYEENICKNAME",
        "value": "Beneficiary nickname"
      }
    ]
  } </pre>
</div>
</div>
