<p><br></p>
<p><span style=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><u><strong>Feb 2026 ERM:</strong>=
</u> As part Payment Initiation V1 to V2 CAP API migration, following reque=
st attributes will be included/added under </span><strong style=3D"letter-s=
pacing: 0.0px;">supplementaryData</strong><span style=3D"letter-spacing: 0.=
0px;">. These will be mapped with the values based on the <a href=3D"https:=
//confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/ARTC/exp-galaxy-payment-v2#expgalax=
ypaymentv2-8.2.Responses" rel=3D"nofollow">aliasLookup response</a>&nbsp;th=
at gets called in make a payment page.</span></p>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(59,65,81);">aliasResolutionTime</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(59,65,81);">aliasRegistrationTime</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(59,65,81);">aliasLastUpdateTime</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(59,65,81);">And the following request attribut=
es will no longer be required as part of <span>Payment Initiation V1 to V2 =
CAP API migration, so the same will be taken out from the EXP API request b=
ody.</span></span></p>
<ul>
<li>$paymentInformation.controlSum</li>
<li>$.paymentTypeInformation.localInstrument</li>
<li>$.creditTransferTransactionInformation[0].supplementaryData.templateId<=
/li>
<li><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"47680758-6744-4ff9-83=
a9-1bb74e98b648">$.creditTransferTransactionInformation[0].paymentTypeInfor=
mation.categoryPurpose</span></li>
<li>$.creditTransferTransactionInformation[0].paymentTypeInformation.localI=
nstrument</li>
<li><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"026e5c7a-9970-4ff7-90=
02-b39a2fd9d6b7">$.creditTransferTransactionInformation[0].paymentTypeInfor=
mation.serviceLevel</span></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><u><strong>May 2026 ERM changes assoc=
iated with Confirmation of Payee:</strong></u> As part of CoP feature, if C=
oP validation is performed by a maker when initiating a payment to a new be=
neficiary, the CoP validation matched status Outcome should be included as =
part of the "supplementaryData" in the EXP API request so that the CoP vali=
dation outcome can be displayed in the payments details authorisation scree=
n</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Account name as returned by the CoP c=
heck will be added to the request payload, and it's only required at the EX=
P API level. (not passing on to the CAP API)</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">As per requirement it is needed to&nb=
sp;be displayed in checker screen.</span></p>
</div></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p><br></p>
