<h1 id=3D"expgalaxypaymentv2-6.Capability:Retrievingapaymentdetails"><span>=
6. Capability: Retrieving a payment details</span></h1>
<p><br></p>
<h2 id=3D"expgalaxypaymentv2-POST/paymentDetails">&nbsp;POST /paymentDetail=
s</h2>
<p>This endpoint returns a details of a payment.</p>
<p><br></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><u><strong>May 2026 ERM:</strong></=
u> As part of async payment processing approach(SD: <a href=3D"https://conf=
luence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/ARTC/Payment+Initiation+using+V2+CAP+API+=
with+Async+approach" rel=3D"nofollow">Payment Initiation using V2 CAP API w=
ith Async approach</a>),&nbsp;</span></p>
<ul>
<li style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);">Che=
ckers will no longer see the final payment outcome immediately after approv=
ing a request. The result will only be available on the <strong>Payment Det=
ails</strong> page.</span></li>
<li style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><sp=
an style=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;">The</span><span style=3D"letter-spacing=
: 0.0px;">&nbsp;</span><strong style=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Payment Det=
ails</strong><span style=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;">&nbsp;</span><span styl=
e=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;">page must be enhanced to display the payment r=
ejection reason, as this information is currently not shown.</span></span><=
/li>
<li style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);">The <strong>Payment Details CAP API</str=
ong> will be enhanced to include the <strong>rejection reason</strong> in i=
ts response.</li>
<li style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);">The=
 <strong>Payment Details EXP API</strong> endpoint will be extended to retu=
rn the <strong>failure reason for RJCT (rejected) payments</strong>.<span s=
tyle=3D"color: rgb(51,102,255);"> <strong>The mapping details TBC as we are=
 still awaiting the details from payments team.</strong></span></span></li>
<li style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><st=
rong>Tentative list of response codes:<br></strong></span>
<ul>
<li style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><a =
style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);" href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.a=
u/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=3D2242753133" rel=3D"nofollow">Error Code Ma=
pping for Async Response Feature - Westpac One Core - Westpac Enterprise Co=
nfluence</a></span></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><br></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><u><strong>May 2026 ERM:</strong></=
u> As part of divisions feature(SD: <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westp=
ac.com.au/display/ARTC/SD%3A+Sub-Orgs%28Divisions%29+Channels#SD:SubOrgs(Di=
visions)Channels-PaymentDetails-Sentforprocessing(PODS)tab" rel=3D"nofollow=
">SD: Sub-Orgs(Divisions) Channels - PaymentDetails-Sentforprocessing(PODS)=
tab</a>),&nbsp;</span></p>
<ul>
<li style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);">The=
 endpoint will be extended to call the PDP query API (<code>GetDivisionsFro=
mPDPQueryResult</code>) to retrieve the divisions for the logged-in user. T=
he division name will be determined by matching the&nbsp;<code>divisionId</=
code>&nbsp;from the PODS payment details CAP API response with the division=
 list returned by PDP.</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><span>The</span><span> division na=
me will be included in the EXP API response payload. <span style=3D"color: =
rgb(51,102,255);"><strong>The mapping details TBC as we are still awaiting =
the details from payments team.</strong></span></span></span></li>
</ul>
