<h1 id=3D"expgalaxypaymentv2-7.Capability:Retrievelistofpaymentsbasedonacco=
untnumber"><span>7. Capability: Retrieve list of payments based on account =
number</span></h1>
<h2 id=3D"expgalaxypaymentv2-POST/paymentListing"><span style=3D"font-size:=
 20.0px;letter-spacing: -0.008em;">POST /paymentListing</span></h2>
<p>This endpoint returns a list of a payment for a given account number and=
 bsb</p>
<p><br></p>
<p><u><strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,102,255);">May 2026 ERM Changes:=
</span> </strong></u><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,255);">This is in relati=
on with downstream endpoint which uses the new <strong>/payments/search</st=
rong> endpoint on page load and when performing a search from EXP API. The =
deprecated&nbsp;<strong>payments/paymentId</strong> downstream API will no =
longer function after the May release.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,255);">While making a request from EXP API=
 to downstream dateTimeRange structure will now look like this and all the =
other params will be as is.</span></p>
<pre class=3D"body-param__example microlight"><br></pre>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">  "dateT=
imeRange": {
    "fromDateTime": "2026-03-16T00:49:14.106Z",
    "toDateTime": "2026-03-16T00:49:14.106Z"
  }</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><u><strong>Feb 2026 ERM changes rel=
ated to divisions:</strong></u></span> <span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"=
>This endpoint will be extended to include an additional query string param=
eter "divisionId". If this query string parameter is supplied as part of th=
e request, the EXP API will pass the same to PODS(in combination with Org C=
ISKey + division Id) to retrieve the payment list from PODS for the supplie=
d division id. Also, this end point will be extended to consume "<strong>Ge=
tDivisionsFromPDPQueryResult</strong>" and "<strong>GetAccountIdsFromPDPQue=
ryResult</strong>" PDP query APIs to meet to the payment list requirements =
as per the sequence flow here: <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.co=
m.au/display/ARTC/SD%3A+Sub-Orgs%28Divisions%29+Channels#SD:SubOrgs(Divisio=
ns)Channels-Paymentstatus-Sentforprocessing" rel=3D"nofollow">SD: Sub-Orgs(=
Divisions) Channels - Paymentstatus-Sentforprocessing</a></span></p>
