. The proposal is to have a single string encoded value with the below attr=
ibutes to start off with. Other attributes can be added as the need arises<=
/p><p>TYPE: app | browser, PLATFORM: ios | andriod | windows | linux | maco=
s, VIEWPORT: xs | sm | md | lg, ORIENTATION: portrait | landscape</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color=
: rgb(59,65,81);">x-originatingSystemId</span></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><span><span class=3D"emoji-common-main-styles emoji-common-node   emoji-=
common-emoji-image   css-19bdfyn" title=3D":white_check_mark:">:tick:</span=
></span></p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><span style=3D"co=
lor: rgb(59,65,81);"><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://one.dev1.ui=
.westpac.com.au/npm/docs/ui-framework/1.7.3/core/api-client/index.html" rel=
=3D"nofollow">ApiClient<span>&nbsp;</span></a>helper will inject this heade=
r parameter.</span></p><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(59,65,81);">This will a=
lways correspond to the Alfabet id of the main consuming SPA although vario=
us micro-frontends and widgets may have separate ownership.</span></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(59,65,81);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,51,51=
);"><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-current">FEB2026</s=
pan></span></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(59,65,81);">protected-orgId</span></p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><span><span class=3D"emoji-common-main-styles emoji-common-node   emoji-=
common-emoji-image   css-19bdfyn" title=3D":white_check_mark:">:tick:</span=
></span></p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p style=3D"text-align: left;"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><strong>P=
attern</strong>: ^(\d{11})$<br>
 This is an organisation CIS Key</span></p>
<p style=3D"text-align: left;"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><strong>N=
ote</strong>:<br>
 This header is used to send the query parameter organisation CIS Key. This=
 header is provided as an alternative standard in the event that an API nee=
ds to handle PII within the URI. More info<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=3D"htt=
ps://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/Pattern+19%3A+API+Endpoint+=
Design+Patterns#Pattern19:APIEndpointDesignPatterns-Pattern19.3.5-UsingHead=
erstoavoidexposingsensitiveinformationintheURIandquerystrings" rel=3D"nofol=
low">read here</a></span></p>
<p style=3D"text-align: left;"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><span sty=
le=3D"color: rgb(51,51,51);"><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lo=
zenge-current">FEB2026</span> division changes: The org CIS Key is required=
 to query PODS when retrieving the payment list from PODS based on the divi=
sionId.</span></span></p>
</div></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
