<h1 id=3D"expgalaxypaymentv2-8.Capability:LookupaPayIDAlias"><span>8. Capab=
ility: <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/pages/viewpage.acti=
on?pageId=3D1812393402" rel=3D"nofollow">Look up a PayID Alias</a>&nbsp;</s=
pan></h1>
<h2 id=3D"expgalaxypaymentv2-POST/alias/lookup"><span>POST /<span class=3D"=
opblock-summary-path" style=3D"color: rgb(59,65,81);">alias/lookup</span></=
span></h2>
<p>This endpoint returns a list of a payment for a given account number and=
 bsb</p>
<p><br></p>
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-current">FEB 26</spa=
n>&nbsp; Either beneficiary id or pay id needs to be supported. For existin=
g beneficiary Pay ID resolution is not getting counted by Pay ID counter, a=
nd beneficiary id will be passed as the request parameter. ( So no one can =
tamper the API with non-existing beneficiary / Pay ID ) For new beneficiary=
 Pay ID related fields need to be supplied and Pay ID counter needs to be t=
riggered.</p>
