<h1 id=3D"expgalaxypaymentv2-10.Capability:Retrievingalistofbeneficiaries">=
<span style=3D"color: rgb(51,102,255);"><strong>10. Capability:<span class=
=3D"fabric-text-color-mark"> Retrieving a list of beneficiaries&nbsp;</span=
></strong></span></h1>
<p><br></p>
<h2 id=3D"expgalaxypaymentv2-POST/beneficiaryList"><span>POST /<span style=
=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">beneficiaryList</span></span></h2>
<p>This endpoint retrieves all <span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">benefi=
ciaries </span>that the user is entitled to and only return accounts / bene=
ficiaries.</p>
<p><br></p>
<p><u><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><strong>Feb 2026 ERM changes rel=
ated to divisions:</strong></span></u> <span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"=
>If divisionId is suppled as part of the request body, the endpoint will pa=
ss it to the GetBeneficiaryIdsFromPdpQueryResult API to retrieve beneficiar=
y IDs specific to that division and if the divisionId is not supplied as pa=
rt of the request body, existing logic will continue to apply. This extende=
d endpoint will be used in the following flow as part of divisions feature:=
 <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/ARTC/SD%3A+Sub-Or=
gs%28Divisions%29+Channels#SD:SubOrgs(Divisions)Channels-MakeaPayment/Trans=
ferfunds" rel=3D"nofollow">SD: Sub-Orgs(Divisions) Channels - MakeaPayment/=
Transferfunds</a></span></p>
<p><br></p>
<div id=3D"expander-296076344" class=3D"expand-container">
