<h3 id=3D"expgalaxypaymentv2-13.4.DownstreamAPIInfo">13.4. Downstream API I=
nfo</h3>
<p>This route should consume the following CAP API,</p>
<ul>
<li>CAP API <em style=3D"text-align: left;">payment-limits-service-v1</em><=
em>, route </em>POST <em>v1/limit-check</em></li>
<li>CAP API Request:&nbsp;=20
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom">
<b class=3D"code-title"></b><span class=3D"collapse-source expand-control" =
style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand-control-icon icon">&nbsp;</sp=
an><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand source</span></span><span cla=
ss=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Midnight; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Midnig=
ht">{
    "instructionIdentification": "d0868661-b955-4e76-9f15-d97626f7df6b",
    "scheme": "NPP",
    "userCISKey": "123456789",
 &nbsp; &nbsp;"userIAMId": "string",
&nbsp; &nbsp; "organisationCISKey": "987654321",
    "settlementAmount": {
        "value": "10000",
        "currencyCode": "AUD"
    }
}</pre>
</div>
</div></li>
<li>CAP API response:=20
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom">
<b class=3D"code-title"></b><span class=3D"collapse-source expand-control" =
style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand-control-icon icon">&nbsp;</sp=
an><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand source</span></span><span cla=
ss=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Midnight; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Midnig=
ht">Response status code : 200
Response body when no limits are breached
{
    "data": {
        "isSuccess": true
    }
}

Response status code : 200
Response body when one or more limits are breached
{
    "data": {
        "isSuccess": false
    },
    "result": {
        "errors": [
            {
                "code": 2302,
                "message": "Limit breaches for user transaction amount",
                "details": "Settlement amount must be lower than the user's=
 maximum transaction limit 1000.00"
            },
            {
                "code": 2303,
                "message": "Limit breaches for user daily amount",
                "details": "Settlement amount must be lower than the user's=
 maximum daily limit 5000.00"
            }
        ]
    }
}</pre>
</div>
</div></li>
</ul>
