<h1 id=3D"expgalaxypaymentv2-14.Capability:Retrievearrangementdetailsforthe=
suppliedaccountIds(Nov2025ERM)"><strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,102,25=
5);">14. Capability:</span><span class=3D"fabric-text-color-mark"><span sty=
le=3D"color: rgb(51,102,255);"> Retrieve arrangement details for the suppli=
ed account Ids</span><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);">(Nov 2025 ERM)</s=
pan></span></strong></h1>
<h2 id=3D"expgalaxypaymentv2-POST/arrangementDetails">POST /arrangementDeta=
ils</h2>
<p>This endpoint retrieves the arrangement details for the supplied list of=
 account IDs as part of the request body. <span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);=
">"Account Holder" is a mandatory property/attributes for payment initiatio=
n, so on selecting "From" &amp; "To" accounts from the typeahead component,=
 make an explicit call to this API route(<a href=3D"#expgalaxypaymentv2-POS=
T/arrangementDetails">POST/arrangementDetails</a></span>)<span style=3D"col=
or: rgb(0,0,0);"> &amp; pass the selected account ids(BSB &amp; account num=
ber) to fetch the arrangement details for the respective accounts &amp; map=
 the "entityName" response attribute/property against the Account Holder. T=
his route is required as part of "uplift max load size for business require=
ment 3(BR.03)", refer to the associated SD here: <a href=3D"/pages/viewpage=
.action?pageId=3D2041141342">SD : Uplift maximum load size for different li=
stings &amp; warn user when more records are available</a> for details.</sp=
an></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size: 16.0px;font-weight: bold;letter-spacing: -0.00=
6em;">14.1 Request</span></p>
<p>Query Parameter</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"relative-table wrapped confluenceTable" style=3D"width: 52.=
5106%;">
<colgroup class=3D"">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 16.4863%;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 11.4136%;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 26.0997%;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 46.0004%;">
</colgroup>
<tbody class=3D"">
<tr class=3D"">
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Name</str=
ong></p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Required<=
/strong></p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Values</s=
trong></p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Descripti=
on</strong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><br></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,51,51);"><span class=3D"inline-comment-mark=
er" data-ref=3D"cd318f7b-45db-4c8c-a939-2beba5f56b0e">arrangementStatus</sp=
an></span></p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p>:cross:</p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><span><code>ACTIVE</=
code>&nbsp; , <code>ACTIVE_AND_INACTIVE</code>&nbsp;</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>&nbsp;<span style=3D"color: rgb(51,51,51);">&=
nbsp;"ACTIVE" will fetch accounts which are active only. <br><br>
 "ACTIVE_AND_INACTIVE " will fetch account swhich are Active and Inactive b=
oth. <br><br>
 If caller is not passing this query parameter then default option of ACTIV=
E assumed downstream</span></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>Header Parameters</p>
