<h3 id=3D"expgalaxypaymentv2-17.3Downstreamchanges(aspartofFeb2026divisionf=
eature)"><span>17.3 </span><span style=3D"letter-spacing: -0.006em;">Downst=
ream changes(as part of</span><span style=3D"letter-spacing: -0.006em;">&nb=
sp;</span><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);">Feb 2026 division feature</s=
pan><span style=3D"letter-spacing: -0.006em;">)</span></h3>
<p><span style=3D"letter-spacing: -0.006em;"><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,4=
3,77);">If<span>&nbsp;</span></span><code>divisionId</code><span style=3D"c=
olor: rgb(23,43,77);"><span>&nbsp;</span>is included in the request body, t=
he endpoint will pass it to the<span>&nbsp;</span></span><code>GetAccountId=
sFromPdpQueryResult</code><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span>&nbsp=
;</span>API to retrieve account IDs specific to that division, following re=
quest body will come into play when calling<span><code>GetAccountIdsFromPdp=
QueryResult</code></span></span><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span=
>&nbsp;</span>API with divisions. Please note: There will be no change in t=
he<span><code>GetAccountIdsFromPdpQueryResult</code></span></span><code><sp=
an>&nbsp;</span></code><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">API response, =
the response payload structure will continue to remain the same.</span></sp=
an></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom">
<b class=3D"code-title"></b><span class=3D"collapse-source expand-control" =
style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand-control-icon icon">&nbsp;</sp=
an><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand source</span></span><span cla=
ss=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
